//! TPM 2.0 key store implementation
//!
//! Implements the `KeyStore` trait using raw TPM 2.0 device I/O via
//! `/dev/tpmrm0`. Keys are generated inside the TPM under the Storage
//! Root Key (SRK) and persisted as wrapped blobs on disk.
//!
//! # Architecture
//!
//! ```text
//! ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
//! │              TpmKeyStore                     │
//! │  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐  │
//! │  │TPM Device │  │SRK Handle│  │Blob Store │  │
//! │  │/dev/tpmrm0│  │0x81000001│  │  {dir}/   │  │
//! │  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  │ *.blob     │  │
//! │                               │ *.json     │  │
//! │                               └───────────┘  │
//! └──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
//! ```
//!
//! # Key Lifecycle
//!
//! 1. `generate_key()` → `TPM2_Create` under SRK → save blob + metadata
//! 2. `sign()` → `TPM2_Load` blob → `TPM2_Sign` → `TPM2_FlushContext`
//! 3. `public_key_der()` → parse stored public area → convert to SPKI DER
//!
//! # Supported Algorithms
//!
//! Native TPM signing: ECDSA P-256, ECDSA P-384, RSA 2048/3072/4096.
//! PQC algorithms are not supported by TPM 2.0 hardware.
//!
//! # Security Model
//!
//! - Private keys never leave the TPM in cleartext
//! - Wrapped blobs are encrypted under the SRK (bound to this TPM chip)
//! - Load-sign-evict pattern minimizes key exposure in TPM transient memory

